Key Match Events: The Utah Jazz kept it close with the Phoenix Suns but ultimately lost 114-106.
Phoenix led by as much as 16 points and Utah never held a lead.
Lauri Markkanen led the way for Utah with 24 points.
Collin Sexton and Walker Kessler were the next highest scorers with 20 and 16 points respectively.
The Jazz cut the deficit down to one point in the third quarter but could not turn things around.
Cody Williams had a career night with notable performances throughout the game.
Will Hardy challenged an out-of-bounds call against the Jazz, which was unsuccessful and resulted in a foul for Kessler and two free throws for Beal.
Pre-Game Insights: The Utah Jazz were missing several key players due to injuries, including Johnny Juzang, Brice Sensabaugh, Jordan Clarkson, John Collins, and Keyonte George.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Elijah Harkless made his NBA debut during the game.
The Jazz will return to Delta Center for a two-game homestand to host the Nets and the Hornets.
